Defendant Steven James Gallob in court with attorney Michael B Plaisted.  Defendant Steven James Gallob in custody.  Kimberly D Schoepp appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  The Court sentenced the defendant as follows:

The Court imposed 12 months at the House of Correction, with Huber for work only; good time allowed.  Credit for 63 days time served.  Court stayed said sentence and placed defendant on probation for two (2) years.  
 * Courrt ordered defendant to provide a DNA sample.
 * Court ordered 4 year driver's license revocation and three (3) years ignitition interlock.
 * Complete a driver assessment and safety plan; order signed and filed; copy provided to defendant.
 * Court ordered defendant to pay a $1,200.00 fine while on probation.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
 - Undergo a mental health evaluation; follow thru with any treatment recommended;
 - No controlled substances, other than those legally prescribed for defendant by a duly licensed physician for his mental or physical needs; take as prescribed and only for as long as deemed medically reasonable and necessary;
 - No alcohol;
 - Urine screens;
 - AODA assessment; treatment if needed;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Be given job and vocational training;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - Parenting classes/counseling;
 - Serve 90 days condition time at the House of Correction, with Huber for work only; good time allowed;
 - Court ordered defendant to pay the fine, the DNA surcharge, plus costs and disbursements, as well as supervision fees. Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant which is non-dischargable in bankruptcy.

